      "content": "If you are truly empty, your body is already in a state where it needs careful management, not a complete shutdown of your insulin. To avoid that 3 AM scare, I strongly advise you to take a very small, conservative basal dose, perhaps just 25% of your usual amount, to keep things stable. If you are terrified, you need to be proactive, not passive. A tiny bit of insulin is better than a major crash.",
